<section xmlns:codified="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/codified" xmlns:codify="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/codify" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" containing-doc="D.C. Code">
  <num>47-2884.13</num>
  <heading>Sale of pawn or pledge—Required time of possession.</heading>
  <text>No pawnbroker shall sell a pawn or a pledge until the pawn or the pledge has remained 6 months in the pawnbroker’s possession, unless by consent in writing by the pawner.</text>
  <annotations>
    <annotation type="History">Aug. 6, 1956, 70 Stat. 1042, ch. 970, § 13</annotation>
    <annotation doc="D.C. Law 5-137" type="History">Mar. 13, 1985, D.C. Law 5-137,§ 2(a), 31 DCR 5743</annotation>
    <annotation doc="D.C. Law 19-171" type="History">Sept. 26, 2012, D.C. Law 19-171, § 302, 59 DCR 6190</annotation>
    <annotation type="Prior Codifications">1981 Ed., § 2-1913.</annotation>
    <annotation type="Prior Codifications">1973 Ed., § 2-2013.</annotation>
    <annotation type="Effect of Amendments"><law-cite doc="D.C. Law 19-171">D.C. Law 19-171</law-cite> enacted this subchapter into law.</annotation>
  </annotations>
</section>
